               Covariances, BNL, July 2011                        4249 1451
Covariances from COMMARA-2.0 were adopted for the Mo isotopes.    4249 1451
Here, new sets of covariances were obtained at BNL in 2010 using  4249 1451
the kernel approach in the resonance region and EMPIRE/KALMAN     4249 1451
analysis of experimental data in the fast neutron region.         4249 1451
Dispersion analysis of the evaluated libraries suggest            4249 1451
uncertainties less than 10% for the total, up to 15% for elastic  4249 1451
above 1 MeV and 50% for capture above 1 MeV. The isotopic data    4249 1451
are available for total, elastic (n,2n) and capture so the        4249 1451
elemental measurements were not used. The EMPIRE/KALMAN analysis  4249 1451
was performed using "nuisance" parameters scaling total and       4249 1451
reaction cross sections to account for systematic uncertainties   4249 1451
and meet dispersion guidelines. In addition, 15% uncertainty on   4249 1451
the gamma-strength scaling factor was assumed.                    4249 1451
